    "headline": "DoorDash Stock Jumps on Strong Earnings Report",
    "summary": "Shares of delivery service  DoorDash  rose sharply in premarket trading Thursday after the company beat analysts’ expectations for its first-quarter earnings even though it missed on revenue.  It also beat analyst expectations for gross order value (GOV), which came in a $31.6 billion, versus the $31.5 billion expected.  For the second quarter, it expects GOV to rise to between $32.4 billion and $33.4 billion, in the same range as analyst expectations.",
